# Form Components Guide

## Component Usage

Forms should use the following components from our design system:

- `Select` from [@/components/select](mdc:src/components/select.tsx) for dropdowns
- `Input` and `InputGroup` from [@/components/input](mdc:src/components/input.tsx) for text inputs
- `Button` from [@/components/button](mdc:src/components/button.tsx) for form submission
- `Heading` from [@/components/heading](mdc:src/components/heading.tsx) for page titles

## Form Structure

Forms should follow this structure:
```tsx
<div className="space-y-6">
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
      Label Text
    </label>
    <InputGroup>
      <Input ... />
    </InputGroup>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Textarea Styling

Textareas should use these classes for consistency:
```tsx
className="w-full px-3 py-2 min-h-[150px] rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-zinc-700 border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 text-zinc-950 dark:text-white placeholder:text-zinc-500"
```

## Form Container

Forms should be wrapped in a white container with these classes:
```tsx
className="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6"
```